National Security Advisor Tom Donilon visited China and had productive discussions with senior Chinese officials. He met with President Hu Jintao, Vice President Xi Jinping, Vice Premier Wang Qishan, State Councilor Dai Bingguo, Foreign Minister Yang Jiechi, and Vice Chairman of the Military Commission General Xu Caihou. They discussed the goals of the bilateral relationship and how to achieve them, as well as regional and global issues such as North Korea, Iran, Syria, regional security in Asia, and the rebalancing of the global economy. Donilon emphasized the importance of building a substantive and sustained military-to-military relationship and continuing the human rights dialogue.